            <title>[CASSANDRA-10658] Some DROP ... IF EXISTS incorrectly result in exceptions on non-existing KS</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10658</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;2.1, 2.2 and 3.0 incorrectly throws &lt;tt&gt;InvalidRequestException&lt;/tt&gt; on non-existing keyspace for &lt;tt&gt;DROP TYPE IF EXISTS&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3.0 incorrectly throws &lt;tt&gt;ConfigurationException&lt;/tt&gt; for &lt;tt&gt;DROP AGGREGATE IF EXISTS&lt;/tt&gt; with type arguments.&lt;br/&gt;
3.0 incorrectly throws &lt;tt&gt;ConfigurationException&lt;/tt&gt; for &lt;tt&gt;DROP FUNCTION IF EXISTS&lt;/tt&gt; with type arguments.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
