                            <comment id="14991916" author="snazy" created="Thu, 5 Nov 2015 16:25:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Pushed some commits for&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/snazy/cassandra/tree/10658-drop-if-2.1&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;2.1&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/snazy/cassandra/tree/10658-drop-if-2.2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;2.2&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/snazy/cassandra/tree/10658-drop-if-3.0&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;3.0&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tests triggered &lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/view/Dev/view/snazy/search/?q=snazy-10658-&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;on cassci&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15028379" author="krummas" created="Thu, 26 Nov 2015 08:59:17 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;3.0 incorrectly throws ConfigurationException for DROP AGGREGATE IF EXISTS with type arguments.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;3.0 incorrectly throws ConfigurationException for DROP FUNCTION IF EXISTS with type arguments.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;patch lgtm but could you add tests for these as well?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15029649" author="snazy" created="Fri, 27 Nov 2015 09:12:28 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;could you add tests for these as well?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The ConfigurationException was thrown from &lt;tt&gt;CQL3Type.Raw#prepare(java.lang.String)&lt;/tt&gt; via &lt;tt&gt;DropFunction/AggregateStatement.prepare&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
There are tests in UFTest and AggregationTest (testNonExistingOnes) that check for the correct message.&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;ve changed the test code to check for the exception class as well (pushed to the 3.0 and trunk branches).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15029684" author="krummas" created="Fri, 27 Nov 2015 09:39:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ok, +1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15029712" author="snazy" created="Fri, 27 Nov 2015 10:02:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks!&lt;br/&gt;
